Final working copy from ROC meeting June 20-22. Edited by Iga  
Korneta and Neocles Leontis. Changes include:

1. Added edges for specific nucleoside residues -- adenosine residue,  
guanosine residue, cytidine residue, and uridine residue as  
subclasses of edges for purines and pyrimidines.
2. Added specific atoms for each standard nucleobase, for ribose  
ring, and for phosphate moiety.
3. Made specific atoms parts of specific edges. For example adenine  
N1 atom part of adenosine edge etc.
4. Added 'has functional parent' relation from CheBI to relate  
modified bases to their functional parent nucleobase.
5. Added 'sulfur atom' and 'selenium atom' classes to use with  
modified bases
6. Added functional groups necessary to define modified bases. Placed  
as new 'group' class under 'submolecule'
7.Added two modified ribose ring classes under 'ribose ring' / 'modified
ribose ring';
8. Added a 'modified phosphate moiety' class under 'phosphate moiety';
9. Added over 120 modified nucleobases, nucleosides, nucleotides.  
Placed under new classes under 'purine' and 'pyrimidine' classes --  
'modified purine' and 'modified pyrimidine.'
10. Created and populated new '5prime cap structure' class.
